        <updateDate>2018-01-26T23:16:17Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Currency Optimization, Innovation, and National Savings Act of 2017</b></p>  <p> <p>This bill directs the Government Accountability Office to study the production cost of the one-cent coin and ways the production cost could be lowered while maintaining the utility of the coin.</p> <p>The bill provides for the replacement of $1 notes with $1 coins as the only $1 monetary unit in circulation. Treasury will no longer be authorized to issue $1 notes two years after passage of this bill and the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System shall ensure that all $1 Federal Reserve notes are destroyed within this time.</p> <p>Notwithstanding this bill, $1 Federal Reserve notes shall remain legal tender in the United States.]]></text>
      </summary>
